The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 May is 42,091 (4,871.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 May, there were 97 new confirmed cases (11.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 May, there were 92 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (5 extra cases).
